<section class="section section--alt" id="qb-help-emergency-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who handles it</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A Certified ProAdvisor triages the file and scopes the repair.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Urgent file work is its own discipline. The first job is to keep a damaged file or drive from getting worse &mdash; stop writing to it, preserve a backup if one can be taken safely. Then a Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications looks at what&rsquo;s actually wrong: whether the file can be opened or rebuilt, what data is recoverable, and what it takes to get reconciliation ready before your deadline. From there we scope the work in writing, fixed fee, and tell you honestly what&rsquo;s achievable in the time you have. We prioritize urgent work within business hours &mdash; we don&rsquo;t run a 24/7 line and we don&rsquo;t guarantee a fix by a set time. An Intuit account, login, billing, software-bug, or QuickBooks Online platform-outage issue stays with Intuit.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

